The paper discusses the ways in which a robot can identify an object's inertial parameters, which is a key aspect of robotic grasping and manipulation. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses visual and exploratory methods for estimating inertial parameters, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of inertial parameters in planning and control, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
